'''Write a simple python program to take input from the user and then print it's reverse using negative indexing of extended slicing index
for example, if user inputs ABC then the output will be as CBA.


# The required output is as:
Please input your string
Your inputted string is:  E and ICT Academy
The reverse of the inputted string is:  ymedacA TCI dna E'''

#code

userinput=input("Please input your string\n")
print ("Your input string is: ",userinput)
print ("The reverse of the input string is: ",userinput[::-1])
